Spoiler

Im not using the term but the chemical by the same name:

Germane is the chemical compound with the formula GeH4, and the germanium analogue of methane. It is the simplest germanium hydride and one of the most useful compounds of germanium. Like the related compounds silaneand methane, germane is tetrahedral. It burns in air to produce GeO2 and water. Germane is a group 14 hydride.
